cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or the case study, please cite it as below."
title: "gpu-efficiency-streaming: Real-Time GPU Cost Governance on Confluent Cloud"
abstract: >-
  Real-time detection and forecasting of GPU inference inefficiency (idle-but-allocated and
  saturation) using Confluent Cloud for Apache Flink built-in ML (ML_DETECT_ANOMALIES, ML_FORECAST),
  Schema Registry, and Stream Lineage. Includes a measured case study on IBM Granite 3.3-8B Instruct
  running on an NVIDIA L4.
authors:
  - name: "Lutflow"
    website: "https://lutflow.dev"
version: "0.4.0"
date-released: "2026-06-15"
license: "Apache-2.0"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Lutflow/gpu-efficiency-streaming"
keywords:
  - kafka
  - apache-flink
  - confluent
  - gpu
  - llm-inference
  - vllm
  - anomaly-detection
  - forecasting
  - finops
  - opentelemetry
